"# Basic Blocks

## Text

_**All kinds**_ of **text** styling options are supported. Basic \`text\` blocks are akin to HTML \`<p>\` tags. Text blocks also support a **variety** of ~~_**rich**_~~ text formatting [options](https://twitter.com/transitive_bs).



## Image

![](https://www.notion.so/image/https%3A%2F%2Fs3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com%2Fsecure.notion-static.com%2F2531b0be-14aa-4667-9e49-1e3b66564e52%2Fnotion-ts.png?table=block&id=4cc3051a-bf4d-4951-b3c3-07478a8f9e53&cache=v2)


## Quote

> This is an example quote.


## Toggle

<details>
<summary>This is a toggle.</summary>
This content is hidden. 🤫

</details>


## Callout

> 💻 This is a basic callout. It can contain blocks and _rich text_. 💪


## Divider


---



## Linked Block

_The following block is linked to the content of a global footer block._

